

1. What is the purpose of a breakpoint?

## Pause: acquiring knowledge about a program during its execution.

2. Does the line of code on a breakpoint run when you start debugging?

## No

3. How do we debug the next line of code?

## Step Over: It will run the current line of code, run and stop at the next line of code.

4.What does the step into command do?

## Step Into will step over the method that is about to be invoked, so the debugger will go 
   into that method and continue debugging step-by-step.


5.What is the difference between evaluate expression and evaluate code fragment?

## Evaluate Expression allowsÂ you to type in values and see the results, in the scope of the stopped line.

## Code Fragment allows you to edit a enclosed node of code
